#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Life Span"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Sappasutta"
msgstr "6. A Serpent"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.6:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn4.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ abbhokāse nisinno "
"hoti, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha was meditating in the open during the dark of "
"night, while a gentle rain drizzled down."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.238"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo "
"mahantaṃ sapparājavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the Buddha feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, manifested in the form of a huge serpent king and approached him."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahatī ekarukkhikā nāvā;"
msgstr "Its body was like a huge canoe carved from a single tree."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.3"
msgid "evamassa kāyo hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahantaṃ soṇḍikākiḷañjaṃ;"
msgstr "Its hood was like a large brewer’s sieve."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.5"
msgid "evamassa phaṇo hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahatī kosalikā kaṃsapāti;"
msgstr "Its eyes were like those big bronze dishes from Kosala."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.7"
msgid "evamassa akkhīni bhavanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatā niccharanti;"
msgstr ""
"Its tongue flickered from its mouth like lightning flashes in a thunderstorm."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.9"
msgid "evamassa mukhato jivhā niccharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya saddo hoti;"
msgstr ""
"The sound of its breathing was like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows."

msgctxt "sn4.6:2.11"
msgid "evamassa assāsapassāsānaṃ saddo hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.1"
msgid "“Yo suññagehāni sevati,"
msgstr "“A self-controlled sage frequents"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.2"
msgid "Seyyā so muni attasaññato;"
msgstr "empty buildings for lodging."

# A clear case where carati means"live’, not “wander”.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.3"
msgid "Vossajja careyya tattha so,"
msgstr "It’s appropriate for such a person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:4.4"
msgid "Patirūpañhi tathāvidhassa taṃ."
msgstr "to live there after relinquishing."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.107"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.239"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.1"
msgid "Carakā bahū bheravā bahū,"
msgstr "Though there are lots of creepy crawlies,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ḍaṃsasarīsapā → ḍaṃsasiriṃsapā (bj, s1-3, km) | ḍaṃsā siriṃsapā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.2"
msgid "Atho ḍaṃsasarīsapā bahū;"
msgstr "and lots of flies and snakes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.3"
msgid "Lomampi na tattha iñjaye,"
msgstr "they wouldn’t stir a hair"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:5.4"
msgid "Suññāgāragato mahāmuni."
msgstr "of a great sage in that empty hut."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.1"
msgid "Nabhaṃ phaleyya pathavī caleyya,"
msgstr "Though the sky may split and the earth may quake,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.2"
msgid "Sabbepi pāṇā uda santaseyyuṃ;"
msgstr "and all creatures be stricken with fear;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.3"
msgid "Sallampi ce urasi pakappayeyyuṃ,"
msgstr "and even if an arrow’s aimed at their breast,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.6:6.4"
msgid "Upadhīsu tāṇaṃ na karonti buddhā”ti."
msgstr "the Buddhas take no shelter in attachments.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.6:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī "
"dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!”"
" miserable and sad, vanished right there."
